The unified test-runner allows all (3) regression testsuites to be run with
a single command (run-tests). This can include the unit testsuite, the
expect testsuite and the python testsuite.

To run the testsuites using the unified test-runner:

1) Slurm must first be installed, configured and running.
2) Change directory to the base testsuite directory (containing this README).
3) Review and edit testsuite.conf if necessary.
4) pytest (pytest-3) must be installed in order to run the python testsuite.
5) Execute run-tests with the desired options.

If perldoc is installed, ./run-tests --man can be used to display a man page
for the test-runner.
